n","kjv_def":"righteousness","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"righteousness(92x)"},"G1354":{"id":"G1354","lemma":"Διονύσιος","translit":"Dionýsios","derivation":"from (Bacchus);","strongs_def":"reveller; Dionysius, an Athenian","kjv_def":"Dionysius","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Dionysius(1x)"},"G1340":{"id":"G1340","lemma":"διϊσχυρίζομαι","translit":"diïschyrízomai","derivation":"from G1223 (διά) and a derivative of G2478 (ἰσχυρός);","strongs_def":"to stout it through, i.e. asservate","kjv_def":"confidently (constantly) affirm","pos":"verb"},"G1375":{"id":"G1375","lemma":"διωγμός","translit":"diōgmós","derivation":"from G1377 (διώκω);","strongs_def":"persecution","kjv_def":"persecution","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"persecution(10x)"},"G1316":{"id":"G1316","lemma":"διαχωρίζομαι","translit":"diachōrízomai","derivation":"from G1223 (διά) and the middle voice of G5563 (χωρίζω);","strongs_def":"to remove (oneself) wholly, i.e. retire","kjv_def":"depart","pos":"verb","usage":"depart(1x)"},"G1309":{"id":"G1309","lemma":"διαφεύγω","translit":"diapheúgō","derivation":"from G1223 (διά) and G5343 (φεύγω);","strongs_def":"to flee through, i.e. escape","kjv_def":"escape"},"G1349":{"id":"G1349","lemma":"δίκη","translit":"díkē","derivation":"probably from G1166 (δεικνύω);","strongs_def":"right (as self-evident), i.e. justice (the principle, a decision, or its execution)","kjv_def":"judgment, punish, vengeance","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"vengeance(2x), judgment(1x)"},"G1314":{"id":"G1314","lemma":"διαφυλάσσω","translit":"diaphylássō","derivation":"from G1223 (διά) and G5442 (φυλάσσω);","strongs_def":"to guard thoroughly, i.e. protect","kjv_def":"keep","pos":"verb","usage":"keep(1x)"},"G1380":{"id":"G1380","lemma":"δοκέω","translit":"dokéō","derivation":"a prolonged form of a primary verb, (used only in an alternate in certain tenses;","strongs_def":"compare the base of G1166 (δεικνύω)) of the same meaning; to think; by implication, to seem (truthfully or uncertainly)